    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-07T08:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-07T08:41:00-05:00" n="319"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.6363/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-07T15:00:00+01:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1920—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. Department’s mail instruction 1162 and my telegram number 150, July 2nd<note
                        n="7" xml:id="d319fn7">Latter not printed.</note> regarding oil situation
                    Netherland Indies. For my <pb facs="0371" n="271" xml:id="pg_271"/> own guidance
                    in discussing the matter with the Foreign Office I should be glad to know
                    whether the present policy of the Netherlands of “Government reserve” (which
                    however when applied to exploitation agreements makes no apparent distinction
                    between Dutch citizens and foreigners) is a cause for proper retaliation on our
                    part inasmuch as the laws of the United States do not exclude foreigners from
                    participation in the development of the petroleum resources of the United
                    States. Please cable reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
